reviews.text: Walked in to pick up my order and was told my total. Was asked cash or card, I said card, they added $3 to my order. I informed them it was a debit card and they‚Äôre not able to assess additional fees (surcharge) when accepting a debit card. The surly woman working there said it doesn‚Äôt matter. I left and went down the street to another pizza place. If you‚Äôve been assessed surcharge on your debit card here I would urge you to dispute these charges at your bank, you will get your money back.

Manager at this store ( Market St) was absolutely horrible! She needs to be fired! Pulled up in my driveway literally blasting her music, rude to my kids and didnt allow my daughter to sign the receipt‚Ä¶ she shoved her out pizza and said ‚Äúshe don‚Äôt have time to wait‚Äù really!? I called the store and complained‚Ä¶to find out she (manager) was the one who did it‚Ä¶ she‚Äôs very rude!  I have called corporate! A manager of a store should always set an example for others.. rather it‚Äôs good or bad! I will NEVER order food from this place again. I rather order from nasty Pizza Hut and accept better customer service! I hate I had to even give a 1 star to leave a review‚Ä¶ she deserves a -negative star and get fired. She lucky I gave my life back to Christ! Otherwise she would have felt my wrath!

So my wife and I ordered two pizzas on 6/3 with chicken, pineapple and jalape√±os I get home and it‚Äôs pepperoni instead of chicken my family and I don‚Äôt eat pork. I called the store to complain to the manager ‚ÄúBarbie‚Äù, she stated that she would give us a credit for the pizzas because we were not about to be inconvenienced and have to drive all the way back to the store. So I called on 6/4 To use my credit and then she tells me it‚Äôs only a credit for one pizza instead of two. She gets rude and impatient yelling asking me if I‚Äôm gonna take the credit or not, and then hangs up the phone on me After I asked her for her managers number. She said that she‚Äôs a general manager after I asked to speak to a general manager immediately, How rude can one be. I‚Äôm sick of people in customer service being absolutely disrespectful. This is not someone who needs to be working at this store let alone claim she is a ‚Äúgeneral manager‚Äù we have spent a lot of money at this store and will not be back if she is still working here!!!! NEVER AGAIN.
The BBQ chicken pizza and parmesan poppers were tasty. A flash size is good for 1 person, while a small is better for 2+ people.

Love the pizzas and italian subs here!

The above review was left over a year ago along with a 5 star review.

This had been our pizza and sub to go spot for many years. However within the past year, the quality/quantity of what comes on the Italian Sub has diminished significantly. This was, WAS our go to spot for the Italian Sub. The flavor is still fantastic but the amount of ingredients that go on it has drastically changed to almost non existent.  The pizzas are still fantastic but we will not be going here for subs anymore. My husband was told over a month ago that they did cut back on ingredients due to availability/cost. And the person he spoke to asked for us to please come back again. So we decided to order last night. My husband called it in and spoke to Renee when he ordered. He explained what happened with our prior experience and asked for plenty of lettuce, tomatoes and onion. She said that wouldn't be a problem. We get our subs and are yet again extremely disappointed. Like I stated above this has been our go to for "The Italian Sub" for many years.
A friend of ours called in and spoke to Renee, while she was apologetic she said they weigh their proportions out to corporate standards.  If the below standard is their standard then they have lost us as customers.
Please do better!!

editorial_summary.overview: Chain pizzeria outlet for build-your-own Chicago-style deep-dish pies, plus wings & subs.

detailedReviews.author: Kay Ference
detailedReviews.text: Truly disappointed their service. I placed an online order to be delivered at 5:30pm. At 5:45pm I called the store and was told that the order was canceled because I placed the order for the wrong store. But, I did not, as the receipt listed the correct store. Then, when I told the person that the receipt showed that I placed the order at the correct store, she then said a man called and canceled the order. The worker also said something about the driver saying the order was canceled. So, I have no idea what they did or why she kept making up stories about the order being canceled. I have been charged $77 for this order and was told it will take up to 5-7 business days for a refund to go through.  In addition to the poor service, there is also a $4.99 delivery charge and an approximate $3.00 credit card charge added to the order, with an expected tip to be added for the driver also. You have permanently lost our business.

detailedReviews.author: owen allen
detailedReviews.text: In my opinion, the best pizza in Akron.  I get delivery from here any time we have a celebration and the pizza you get is top notch.  The pan pizza has a nice, thick crust, with a good crunch on the bottom and a pillowy center; it usually has plenty of sauce and cheese, and they have really good prices for it ($12 for a large pepperoni!).  Their garlic cheese bread is a necessary addition, and get a bunch of marinara sauce to dip everything in, I would inject that stuff directly into my veins if I could.  The delivery guy is also the best guy ever, I swear he is always a joy to talk to.  If you're ordering pizza in Akron, get it from here, you will not be disappointed!

detailedReviews.author: Derek Beltz
detailedReviews.text: Ordered their Chicago Style Deep Dish for dinner last night.  The young man on the phone told me "Ya know there's sauce on top of that" to which I informed him that yes, that's what makes it a deep dish Chicago pizza.  He took my info then promptly hung up on me during mid sentence. When I picked up the pizza there were a few young kids in the open window kitchen just standing around and one girl was on her cell phone the whole time.  When I got home and looked at my pizza there was little to no sauce at all on top.  (It used to be covered in marinara and grated Parmesan cheese.  Since it was too late to return I begrudgingly ate a slice feeling very disappointed. I don't think I'll be going back there again. I should have just ordered from Romeo:s.  ...at least they know how to make a deep dish.

detailedReviews.author: C. C.
detailedReviews.text: I ordered a thin crust pizza. What I got wasn't a thin crust pizza. The flavor of the crust and pizza overall was good. However, if you want a thin crust pie, this isn't the place. I provided them feedback and hope they stop labeling their pizza thin crust when it isn't. For those who have no issue with the thickness of the crust, I highly recommend East of Chicago Pizza. I sought the opinion of two others, and they agreed this was not a thin crust. The 3 star rating is because of the crust issue. Pizza restaurants should know this difference.

detailedReviews.text: Honestly I just don't like it.

detailedReviews.author: Nicholas Liodos
detailedReviews.text:
This location's pizza has the classic East of Chicago flavor every time I order. Professional and polite staff who get the food done on time without the quality of their work suffering. I have been ordering pizza here for more than half a decade and it tastes the same every time.
Consistently good food, punctual reliability, and the atmosphere inside projects cleanliness and tidiness. Been my #1 for several years, highly recommended.
Don't forget; to ask about specials for a good deal, whether you're eating alone or feeding a family, you can count on a good meal from this place.
